{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Professionals to receive mandatory training around Carers and their needs",
        "additional_details": "\u2018There are around 7 million Carers in the U.K. - that is one in ten people!\u2019 (Carers.org) \r\n\r\nProfessionals having mandatory training would give them the knowledge they need in order to help, support and identify Carers earlier. \r\n\r\nUnpaid Carers are not valued - Let\u2019s change this!",
        "background": "There is continuing to be a significant increase in unpaid Carers coming forward for help and support. However, some Carers feel unable to ask for help, therefore, professionals identifying a Carer is extremely important. \r\nUnfortunately, a lot of professionals lack the knowledge of Carers.",
